      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Fix Discord default account startup priority",
        "body": "Fixes #77429\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior or issue addressed: Discord multi-account startup delay ordering previously followed the configured account id list directly, so a configured primary account such as `channels.discord.defaultAccount: \"main\"` could be assigned a delayed startup slot when secondary account ids sorted before it.\n\nReal environment tested: local OpenClaw checkout at `/Users/andy/openclaw` on macOS, branch `codex/77429-discord-default-startup-fix`, using the production Discord channel gateway startup path in `extensions/discord/src/channel.ts` with the existing Discord channel test harness.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```console\n$ pnpm exec oxfmt --write extensions/discord/src/channel.ts extensions/discord/src/channel.test.ts\n$ pnpm test:extension discord extensions/discord/src/channel.test.ts\n$ env OPENCLAW_TSGO_HEAVY_CHECK_LOCK_HELD=1 node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.extensions.test.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/extensions-test.tsbuildinfo\n$ git diff --check -- extensions/discord/src/channel.ts extensions/discord/src/channel.test.ts\n```\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n```text\npnpm test:extension discord extensions/discord/src/channel.test.ts\nTest Files  160 passed (160)\nTests       1743 passed (1743)\n\nenv OPENCLAW_TSGO_HEAVY_CHECK_LOCK_HELD=1 node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.extensions.test.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/extensions-test.tsbuildinfo\nexit code 0\n\ngit diff --check -- extensions/discord/src/channel.ts extensions/discord/src/channel.test.ts\nexit code 0\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: the regression test configures `defaultAccount: \"main\"` with account ids ordered as `billy`, `farber`, then `main`. Starting `main` does not call `sleepWithAbort`, while starting `billy` calls the 10s delay and starting `farber` calls the 20s delay. This proves the configured primary account starts immediately even when the previous account ordering would have delayed it, and secondary accounts remain staggered.\n\nWhat was not tested: no live Discord gateway with real bot tokens was started in this checkout; the proof uses the production Discord gateway startup function with mocked provider/probe network calls to isolate startup delay behavior.\n\n## Supplemental validation\n\n- Promotes the resolved Discord default account to the first startup slot only when it is enabled and configured for runtime startup.\n- Preserves existing secondary account stagger behavior after the promoted default account.\n- Does not change Discord usage UI, memory-core, Mattermost, or MCP code.\n",
        "branch": "codex/77429-discord-default-startup-fix",
